  "prompt": "Can pigs show affection?",
  "response": "Yes, pigs can show affection. They are intelligent and social animals with the capability to form strong bonds with other pigs, other animals, and humans. Pigs express affection through various behaviors such as nuzzling, vocalizations, licking, and following their caregivers around. They enjoy physical contact and being near those they trust, often seeking out belly rubs and gentle petting. The ability of pigs to show affection is indicative of their high level of emotional and social intelligence.",
